  "text": "Let k be a number field. Denote by Ω k the set of all places of k. For a smooth and projective k-variety X its Brauer-Manin set is the subset X(A k ) Br of v∈Ω k X(k v ) consisting of those adelic points that are orthogonal to the Brauer group for the Brauer-Manin pairing, cf. [CITATION_1] , II. Chapter 5.",
